But refugees in Dadaab will need much more than luck to turn their fortunes around. They need access to opportunities — mostly education and livelihoods — and the possibility to choose how they want to live. Humanitarian aid has been vital in sustaining Dadaab refugees; it can still support them to transition to a life of dignity.



